cards.title: Big Pharma (Pfizer, J&J, Merck, AbbVie, BMS)
cards.notes:
AbbVie (ABBV) has been performing exceptionally well due to several key factors:

  Key Success Drivers:

  1. Post-Humira Transition Success ðŸŽ¯
  - Skyrizi and Rinvoq (their two blockbuster immunology drugs) generated $17.7B in 2024 (+51% YoY)
  - Successfully replaced revenue lost from Humira's biosimilar competition
  - These drugs are projected to hit $24B in 2025 and exceed $31B by 2029

  2. Strong Financial Performance ðŸ“ˆ
  - Revenue growth rebounded to 6% in Q4 2024 after 2023 decline
  - Ex-Humira drugs growing ~19% in 2024
  - Adjusted EPS of $10.12 in 2024

  3. Impressive 2025 Outlook ðŸš€
  - Guidance: $12.12-$12.32 adjusted EPS (21% increase)
  - Market confidence in continued growth trajectory

  4. Pipeline & Innovation ðŸ’Š
  - Vyalev approved (Nov 2024) - transformative Parkinson's therapy
  - 20+ early-stage deals in immunology, oncology, neuroscience
  - Strong R&D momentum

  5. Attractive Investment Profile ðŸ’°
  - Trading at <16x 2025 earnings (reasonable valuation)
  - 3.3% dividend yield
  - Hit all-time high of $242.63 on October 1, 2025

  Bottom Line:

  AbbVie successfully navigated the "patent cliff" from Humira's biosimilar competition by building a strong immunology franchise with
  Skyrizi/Rinvoq, while maintaining a robust pipeline and rewarding shareholders with dividends.
